@page "/anchor"
<PageTitle>Anchor / Hyperlink - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="anchor">Anchor / Hyperlink</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The A component renders an anchor element. The Hyperlink alias is also available.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <h3>Basic Usage</h3>
            <pre><code>&lt;A Href="https://example.com"&gt;Visit Example&lt;/A&gt;</code></pre>

            <h3>With HyperlinkTarget</h3>
            <pre><code>&lt;A Href="/docs" Target="HyperlinkTarget.Blank"&gt;
    Open in new tab
&lt;/A&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="parameters">Parameters</h2>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Href</td><td>string?</td><td>Link destination URL.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Target</td><td>HyperlinkTarget?</td><td>Link target behavior.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Class</td><td>string?</td><td>Additional CSS classes.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>ChildContent</td><td>RenderFragment</td><td>Link text or content.</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="anchor-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Anchor</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Anchor</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Bootstrap 5, the A component renders as a standard anchor element with
                Bootstrap's link color styles applied through Bootstrap's base CSS. You can
                apply Bootstrap link utility classes such as link-primary, link-secondary, or
                link-underline-opacity-50 through the Specialization parameter to control
                the link color, underline, and hover behavior.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="anchor-daisyui">DaisyUI Anchor</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Anchor</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In DaisyUI, the A component can use the DaisyUI link class and its variants
                such as link-primary, link-secondary, or link-hover. These classes apply
                DaisyUI's theme-aware link colors and underline behavior. Links inside DaisyUI's
                menu component automatically receive the appropriate hover and active styles
                through DaisyUI's CSS without additional class configuration.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="anchor-basecoat">Basecoat Anchor</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Anchor</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Basecoat, the A component is styled with Tailwind utility classes for color,
                underline decoration, and hover states. The default Basecoat anchor style uses
                the theme's primary color with an underline that appears on hover. You can
                override the color, decoration, and transition behavior through Tailwind utilities
                passed via the Class or Specialization parameters.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("anchor", "Anchor / Hyperlink"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("parameters", "Parameters", 2),
    new TocItem("anchor-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5 Anchor", 2, "bootstrap"),
    new TocItem("anchor-daisyui", "DaisyUI Anchor", 2, "daisyui"),
    new TocItem("anchor-basecoat", "Basecoat Anchor", 2, "basecoat")
])" />

</div>
